JOHANNESBURG - The Commission for Gender Equality (CGE) said Jonathan Shapiro s rape cartoon is inappropriate, given South Africa's high levels of sexual violence. The artist, known as Zapiro, drew a cartoon depicting President Jacob Zuma zipping up his pants after presumably raping a woman, who represents South Africa.He then hands her over to a Gupta brother.READ: Gang rape metaphor outrageThe president s allies are seen holding down the woman.The commission said rape can never be normalised and that using the word loosely traumatises rape survivors.The 2016 crime statistics indicate over 50,000 rapes were reported last year.Zapiro has defended his cartoon, saying the rape metaphor was warranted in the current political climate.eNCA